headline: 3 reasons to buy Costco stock and steer clear of Target
summary: Ahead of fresh retail sales data, Tematica Research's chief investment officer, Chris Versace, joins Market Domination with Josh Lipton to compare two top retail plays, Costco (COST) and Target (TGT), on today's Good Buy or Goodbye. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here.

headline: Costco Is One of the Largest Consumer Goods Companies by Market Cap. But Is It a Buy?
summary: Costco has a market cap of $430 billion and an impressive membership base of 140 million.  There are lots of fantastic consumer goods companies for investors to buy these days, many of which have long track records of beating the market and years of solid financial performance.  One of the largest consumer goods companies is Costco Wholesale (NASDAQ: COST), a popular discount warehouse club.
